# Styling & Design Tokens

All colors are centralized as CSS custom properties. Never scatter color definitions across components.

## Single Source of Truth

- All color values defined as CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css` under `@layer base`
- Variables use HSL format without the `hsl()` wrapper: `--primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%`
- Tailwind config maps variables to utility classes: `"hsl(var(--primary))"`
- Dark mode overrides go in a `.dark` selector in the same file

## Naming Convention

- **Base UI colors**: follow shadcn/ui conventions (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--muted`, etc.)
- **Domain-specific colors**: use semantic prefixes (`--status-available`, `--status-occupied`, `--balance-paid`, `--balance-outstanding`)
- Never name colors by their visual appearance (`--green`, `--red`, `--blue`)

## What's Forbidden

- No hardcoded color literals in components (`bg-red-500`, `text-green-600`, `#ff0000`, `rgb(...)`)
- No inline color styles -- always use Tailwind utility classes backed by CSS variables
- No duplicate color definitions -- if a color exists in `globals.css`, don't redefine it elsewhere

## Contrast & Accessibility

- All foreground/background pairings must meet WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text)
- Every `--*` color that serves as a background must have a corresponding `--*-foreground` for text
- Color-coded indicators must also use text or icons (never color alone -- see cross-cutting constraints)
